# Project Guidelines

## File Creation Policy
**CRITICAL**: Do NOT create new files unless explicitly requested by the user. Always ask for permission before creating any new files, including:
- Documentation files (*.md)
- Configuration files
- Test files
- Any other new files

Only create files when the user explicitly asks you to do so.

## Project Structure
- `src/` - Source code modules
- `tools/` - Utility scripts and tools
- `main.py` - Main entry point

## Key Files
- `requirements.txt` - Python dependencies
- `README.md` - Project documentation

## Basic Guidelines
- Follow existing code style and conventions
- Test changes before committing
- Document significant changes
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones

## Common Tasks
- Download data using `tools/download_data.py`
- Run main script with `python main.py`
